@believenu: 39 steps is pre WW2, and not the one you think. Later remake is few years old. The Man Who Knew  Too Much 1956 is the only time when absolute legends, Stewart and Day, played together.
Pillow Talk (1959) and Tea for Two (1950) are my favored Doris Day movies, but unfortunately, never released (or aired) in HDef form.

Digression to what you said few hours ago: your saying "funding Hollywood again" describes what I constantly have in mind. All movies I loved I watched ten, sometimes fifteen times - in theaters. Bought a ticket. I think I've done my share. This "torrenting thing" is payback in my last days (figuratively, I don't plan to drop dead by the end of the week).

@rajmxxx: You requested two movies yesterday. I answered (Anaconda has go, Taxi no-go).

You have slow connection and you cannot seed back decent enough.

Think about - and be reasonable and fair to others.
